# Windows PowerShell shell gotchas

Shell is **PowerShell**, not bash. Path has a space (`Job Guide`) — always double-quote paths.

## No bash heredocs

`<<'EOF'` fails in PowerShell. For multi-line commit/PR bodies: write a temp file with the `Write` tool, then:

```text
git commit -F .git/COMMIT_MSG_TMP.txt
gh pr create --title "..." --body-file .git/PR_BODY_TMP.md
```

Delete the temp file after success. Do not use heredoc, `printf` multi-line, or embedded newlines in `-m`/`--body`.

## Slow / “still running” shells

WMI/`Get-CimInstance` and some git/gh calls are often 25–90s+. Before killing or re-running: `Read` the terminal file for a completion line (hash, `PASS`, URL). Treat as hung only if output is unchanged across two checks **and** no completion signal.

## Prefer file tools

Use `Read`/`Write`/`StrReplace`/`Glob`/`Grep` over PowerShell `cat`/`echo`/`sed`/`dir`/`ls`.
